164	
165	## Relationships
166	- PregnancyProfile has many WeightEntries (1:N via implicit ownership)
167	- PregnancyProfile has many CycleEntries (1:N via implicit ownership)
168	- PregnancyProfile has many MoodEntries (1:N via implicit ownership)
169	- PregnancyProfile has many SymptomEntries (1:N via implicit ownership)
170	- PregnancyProfile has many DoctorVisits (1:N via implicit ownership)
171	- PregnancyProfile has many Reminders (1:N via implicit ownership)
172	- PregnancyProfile has one UserPreferences (1:1)
173	- WeekContent is standalone reference data keyed by weekNumber
174	- Article is standalone reference data (filterable by ArticleTopic)
175	- Exercise is standalone reference data (filterable by ExerciseCategory)
176	- Article references many Articles via relatedArticleIds (N:N self-referential)
177	
178	## Screen to Entity Mapping
179	| Screen | Entities Consumed |
180	|--------|-------------------|
181	| Home | PregnancyProfile, WeightEntry (latest), MoodEntry (latest), Reminder (next), WeekContent (current week) |
182	| Cycle Tracking | CycleEntry, PregnancyProfile |
183	| Weight & Nutrition | WeightEntry, PregnancyProfile, WeekContent (nutrition tips) |
184	| Pregnancy Progress | PregnancyProfile, WeekContent, SelfCareCheckState |
185	| Mindfulness | Exercise, MoodEntry (today) |
186	| Exercise Detail | Exercise |
187	| Health Log | DoctorVisit, SymptomEntry, Reminder |
188	| Mood & Wellness | MoodEntry, PregnancyProfile |
189	| Education | Article |
190	| Article Reader | Article |
191	| Settings | PregnancyProfile, UserPreferences |
192	
193	## Mock Data Requirements
194	- 1 PregnancyProfile (week 22, due date ~18 weeks out, name "Mira")
195	- 15-20 WeightEntries spanning weeks 15-22 (values ~56-59 kg, gradual increase)
196	- 3-5 CycleEntries (pre-pregnancy history)
197	- 10-14 MoodEntries spanning last 2 weeks (mood levels 2-5, energy levels 2-5)
198	- 5-8 SymptomEntries with varied types and severities
199	- 3-4 DoctorVisits with realistic summaries
200	- 4-6 Reminders (mix of done and pending, next checkup in 5 days)
201	- 42 WeekContent entries (one per pregnancy week, with size comparisons, body changes, baby development)
202	- 4 SelfCareCheckState items per day (prenatal vitamins, hydration, kegel exercises, gentle stretching)
203	- 10-15 Articles across all 4 topics
204	- 8-12 Exercises across all 3 categories (breathing, stretching, meditation)
205	- 1 UserPreferences with defaults (kg, all notifications on, reduced motion off)
